<usermanual>
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	

									ATTITUDES TOWARDS CHOCOLATE QUESTIONNAIRE
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

Script Author: Katja Borchert, Ph.D. (katjab@millisecond.com) for Millisecond Software, LLC
Date: 08-02-2016
last updated:  02-17-2022 by K. Borchert (katjab@millisecond.com) for Millisecond Software, LLC

Script Copyright © 02-17-2022 Millisecond Software
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
BACKGROUND INFO 	
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
This script implements the Attitudes towards Chocolate Questionnaire published by:

Benton, D., Greenfield, K. & Morgan, M. (1998). The development of the attitudes to chocolate questionnaire, 
Personality and Individual Differences, 24, 513-520.
(http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0191886997002158)

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
OVERVIEW
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
24 slider questions (0-100 points each)
* 10 Guilt questions
* 10 Craving questions
* 4 Functional questions

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
DURATION 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
the default set-up of the script takes appr. 5 minutes to complete

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
DATA FILE INFORMATION 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
The default data stored in the data files are:

(1) Raw data file: 'attitudestowardschocolatequestionnaire.iqdat'

date, time:						date and time script was run with the current group/subjectnumber 
subject, group, session:	  	with the current subject/groupnumber/session id
build:							the Inquisit build 

q*_response:					response given (in assigned values)
								Scale: 0 (not at all like me) - 100 (very much like me)
								no reversed scored questions
									
q*_latency:						how much time (in ms) the participant spent on the surveypage with this particular 
								question (the last time this particular surveypage was visited)

(2) Summary data file: 'attitudestowardschocolatequestionnaire_summary.iqdat' (Inquisit Lab: one data file per participant)

inquisit.version:			Inquisit version run
computer.platform:			the platform the script was run on (win/mac/ios/android)
startDate:					date script was run
startTime:					time script was started
subjectid:					assigned subject id number
groupid:					assigned group id number
sessionid:					assigned session id number
elapsedTime:				time it took to run script (in ms); measured from onset to offset of script
completed:					0 = script was not completed (prematurely aborted); 
							1 = script was completed (all conditions run)
								
dropdown.gender.response:		the response to the gender question 
								Note: if response is 'other', the data are treated as "female" in this script for percentile rank determinations

Craving:						Craving Score = mean score of all 10 craving (C) questions (0-100)
Craving_percentile:				the percentile of the Craving Score based on normative data published in Table 3, p. 516, in Benton et al (1998)
								and linear interpolation for the gender indicated (!default is female in this script!)
								Note: for Males: the upper score reported is 81.4 (100%) - in this script: anything above 81.4 receives a rank of 100%

Guilt:							Guilt Score = mean score of all 10 guilt (G) questions (0-100)
Guilt_percentile:				the percentile of the Guilt Score based on normative data published in Table 3, p. 516, in Benton et al (1998)
								and linear interpolation for the gender indicated (!default is female in this script!)
								Note: for Males: the upper score reported is 70.6 (100%) and for Females it is 79.5 (100%)- in this script: anything above these scores receives a rank of 100%
																
Functional:						Functional Score = mean score of all 4 functional (F) questions (0-100)
Functional_percentile:			the percentile of the Functional Score based on normative data published in Table 3, p. 516, in Benton et al (1998)
								and linear interpolation for the gender indicated (!default is female in this script!)
								Note: for Males: the upper score reported is 97.0 (100%) and for Females it is 99.7 (100%)- in this script: anything over these scores receives a rank of 100%
									
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
QUESTIONNAIRE SET-UP & SCORING
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
24 slider questions (0-100 points):
* 10 Guilt questions => the mean score is the Guilt Score
* 10 Craving questions => the mean score is the Craving Score
* 4 Functional questions => the mean score is the Functional Score

NORMS
normative data published in Benton et al (1998), p.516 (table 3);
based on N = 330 (Females: N=226; Males: N=104), 
with 
Craving: 
Female: Mean = 46.8 (SD = 21.8); Male: Mean = 29.5 (SD = 19.4)
Guilt: 
Female: Mean = 44.6 (SD = 21.8); Male: Mean = 21.2 (SD = 15.5)
Functional:
Female: Mean = 16.1 (SD = 7.3); Male: Mean = 15.6 (SD = 7.9)

percentiles reported in this script are based on the reported percentile categories and the process of linear interpolation 

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
INSTRUCTIONS 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
can be edited under section EDITABLE PARAMETERS

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
EDITABLE CODE 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
check below for (relatively) easily editable parameters, stimuli, instructions etc. 
Keep in mind that you can use this script as a template and therefore always "mess" with the entire code 
to further customize your experiment.

The parameters you can change are:

/pageinstructions:		the instructions presented on each surveypage

</usermanual>


*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	EDITABLE PARAMETERS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

/pageinstructions:			the instructions that appear at the top of each surveypage

<parameters>
/pageinstructions = "Please answer the following questions by moving the arrow to the appropriate position on each slider.

"
</parameters>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	EDITABLE INSTRUCTIONS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
<instruct>
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 3.00%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ txcolor = (black)
</instruct>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
							REMAINING CODE: Customize after careful consideration only
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	DEFAULTS:
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
requires Inquisit 6.5.2.0

<defaults>
/minimumversion = "6.5.2.0"
/canvasaspectratio = (4,3)
</defaults>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	DATA: this section contains data file information
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

********************
Summary data
********************

<summarydata>
/ columns = (inquisit.version, computer.platform, script.startDate, script.startTime, script.subjectId, script.groupId, script.sessionId, 
script.elapsedTime, script.completed,
dropdown.gender.response,
expressions.Craving, values.Craving_percentile,
expressions.Guilt, values.Guilt_percentile,
expressions.Functional, values.Functional_percentile)
</summarydata>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	VALUES: automatically updated
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

helper variables to determine percentile rank of scores:
/bottom:				stores the bottom border score of the current percentile interval 
/top:					stores the top border score of the current percentile interval 
/bottom_percentile:		stores the bottom percentile of the current percentile category 
/top_percentiles:		stores the top percentile of the current percentile category

/Craving_percentile:	the percentile of the Craving Score based on normative data published in Table 3, p. 516, 
						and linear interpolation in Benton et al (1998)	for the gender indicated (!default is female in this script!)
/Guilt_percentile:		the percentile of the Guilt Score based on normative data published in Table 3, p. 516, 
						and linear interpolation in Benton et al (1998)	for the gender indicated (!default is female in this script!)
/Functional_percentile:	the percentile of the Functional Score based on normative data published in Table 3, p. 516, 
						and linear interpolation in Benton et al (1998)	for the gender indicated (!default is female in this script!)

<values>
/bottom = 0
/top = 0
/bottom_percentile = 0
/top_percentile = 0

/Craving_percentile = ""
/Guilt_percentile = ""
/Functional_percentile = ""
</values>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	EXPRESSIONS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
/Craving:		Craving Score = mean score of all 10 craving (C) questions
/Guilt:			Guilt Score = mean score of all 10 guilt (G) questions
/Functional:	Functional Score = mean score of all 4 functional (F) questions

/calculateStep:		helper function to determine the ratio of difference of top-bottom percentiles to difference in top-bottom scores

/Craving_percentile_F: F=Females => the percentile of the Craving Score based on normative data published in Table 3, p. 516, and linear interpolation in Benton et al (1998)
/Guilt_percentile_F: F=Females =>  the percentile of the Guilt Score based on normative data published in Table 3, p. 516, and linear interpolation in Benton et al (1998)
					Note: the upper limit reported by Benton et a (1998) is a score of 79.5 (percentile rank: 100%)- this script assigns any possible score > 79.9 percentile rank 100%
/Functional_percentile_F: F=Females => the percentile of the Functional Score based on normative data published in Table 3, p. 516 in Benton et al (1998)
					Note: the upper limit reported by Benton et a (1998) is a score of 99.7 (percentile rank: 100%)- this script assigns any possible score > 99.7 percentile rank 100%

(same for M = Males)

/determinePercentiles:	assigns percentile ranks according to gender (default is 'Female' in this script)
					
<expressions>
/Craving = (slider.q1_C.response + slider.q2_C.response + slider.q7_C.response + slider.q8_C.response + slider.q13_C.response + 
slider.q17_C.response + slider.q18_C.response + slider.q21_C.response + slider.q23_C.response + slider.q24_C.response)/10

/Guilt = (slider.q3_G.response + slider.q4_G.response + slider.q6_G.response + slider.q9_G.response + slider.q10_G.response + 
slider.q11_G.response + slider.q14_G.response + slider.q15_G.response + slider.q16_G.response + slider.q22_G.response)/10

/Functional = (slider.q5_F.response + slider.q12_F.response + slider.q19_F.response + slider.q20_F.response)/4

/calculateStep = {
	if (values.top_percentile > values.bottom_percentile) {
		(values.top_percentile-values.bottom_percentile)/(values.top-values.bottom);
	} else {
		0;
	}
}	

/Craving_percentile_F = {
	if (expressions.Craving <= 6.3) {
		values.bottom = 0;
		values.top = 6.3;
		values.bottom_percentile = 0;
		values.top_percentile = 5;
	} else if (expressions.Craving <= 15){
		values.bottom = 6.3;
		values.top = 15;
		values.bottom_percentile = 5;
		values.top_percentile = 10;		
	} else if (expressions.Craving <= 21.3){
		values.bottom = 15;
		values.top = 21.3;
		values.bottom_percentile = 10;
		values.top_percentile = 15;		
	} else if (expressions.Craving <= 26.7) {
